1. Open up a Linux Terminal (Ubuntu)
2. wget https://downloads.apache.org/hive/hive-3.1.2/apache-hive-3.1.2-bin.tar.gz
3. tar xzf apache-hive-3.1.2-bin.tar.gz
4. 'ls' to be sure that you have the uncompressed file in your system.
5. vi ~/.bashrc
6. Insert these lines into the .bashrc file:
    export HIVE_HOME=~/apache-hive-3.1.2-bin
    export $PATH:$HIVE_HOME/bin
7. Exit the vi file editor
8. source ~/.bashrc
9. cd $HIVE_HOME/bin
10. vi hive-config.sh
11. Insert these lines into the hive-config.sh file:
    export HADOOP_HOME=~/hadoop/hadoop-3.3.0
12. Exit the vi file editor
13. cd ~/hadoop/hadoop-3.3.0
14. Start the dfs and yarn daemons:
    sbin/start-dfs.sh
    sbin/start-yarn.sh
15. 'jps' to ensure all daemons are running.
16. hdfs dfs -mkdir /tmp
17. hdfs dfs -chmod 777 /tmp
18. hdfs dfs -mkdir -p /user/hive/warehouse
19. hdfs dfs -chmod g+w /user/hive/warehouse
20. cd $HIVE_HOME
21. cd conf
22. cp hive-default.xml.template hive-site.xml
23. cp hive-env.sh.template hive-env.sh
24. vi hive-site.xml
25. If you type '/' in command mode you can find a string of characters in the file
26. /hive.metastore.warehouse
27. Be sure that the value for 'hive.metastore.warehouse' is set to 'user/hive/warehouse'
28. /&#8
29. Enter insert mode and delete those three characters
30. Press 'esc' to enter command mode
31. /javax.jdo.option.ConnectionURL
32. Where you see 'jdbc:derby:;databsaeName=metastore_db;create=true'
    Delete this text and replace it with 'jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/metastore_db?createDatabaseIfNotExist=true'
33. /javax.jdo.option.ConnectionDriverName
34. Delete 'org.apache.derby.jdbc.EmbeddedDriver' and replace it with 'com.mysql.jdbc.Driver'
35. /ConnectionUserName
36. Delete 'APP' and replace it with 'hive'
37. /ConnectionPassword
38. Delete 'mine' and replace it with whatever you want your password to be (remember it).
39. Exit vi file editor with ':wq'
40. sudo apt-get install mysql-client-core-8.0
41. 'mysql --version' to ensure that it installed correctly.